[
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"253990\">@fitzgen (he/him)</span> I was poking at somethings and noticed that there's a few instances in wasm translation where <code>features.gc()</code> affects what CLIF is generated. Notably <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/5ed24363bebb64ddc41cdc9c90bf8607ef988f5f/crates/cranelift/src/func_environ.rs#L2211\">checking type signatures in call-indirect</a> (and another <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/5ed24363bebb64ddc41cdc9c90bf8607ef988f5f/crates/cranelift/src/func_environ.rs#L2305\">here</a>) changes whether or not GC is enabled.</p>\n<p>I think this is probably something we're going to want to fix prior to enable-by-default (or before we ship on-by-default) because otherwise this looks like it's de-optimizing the <code>call_indirect</code> path with gc enabled. I think this is probably an easy fix (specialize <code>funcref</code> tables specifically) by my read, but wanted to flag this with you</p>",
        "id": 600331983,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Crichton",
        "timestamp": 1780602656
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"253994\">Alex Crichton</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217126-wasmtime/topic/Turning.20on.20GC.20changes.20codegen.20for.20.60call_indirect.60/near/600331983\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>because otherwise this looks like it's de-optimizing the <code>call_indirect</code> path with gc enabled.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The fast path for call-indirect with GC is the same as call-indirect without GC, and the slow path with GC will always result in a trap without GC, so I don't think this is actually de-optimizing anything (other than a very slight bit of code size bloat, which is acceptable in this case IMO)</p>",
        "id": 600526472,
        "sender_full_name": "fitzgen (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1780615050
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The <a href=\"https://godbolt.org/z/Efz5c68cW\">codegen definitely changes though</a>, and notably with <code>-Wgc</code> I see:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cmp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">esi</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">edx</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">sete</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">al</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">movzx</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">eax</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">al</span>\n<span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">test</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">eax</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">eax</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">je</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mh\">0xa2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">wasm</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">]::</span><span class=\"n\">function</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"mh\">0xa2</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 600527773,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Crichton",
        "timestamp": 1780615828
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cmp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">esi</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">edx</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">sete</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">al</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">movzx</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">eax</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">al</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cmp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">esi</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">edx</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">je</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mh\">0x64</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">wasm</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">]::</span><span class=\"n\">function</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"mh\">0x64</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p><em>cries in peephole optimization and path-sensitive constant propagation pain</em></p>\n<p>(<code>eax</code> will always be constant 1 when taken, constant 0 when not -- and after N years of effort our flags-related codegen is still decidedly Not Great. tangential to topic but we definitely still have low-hanging fruit here)</p>",
        "id": 600528529,
        "sender_full_name": "Chris Fallin",
        "timestamp": 1780616329
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I can never get sightglass to do what I want...</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">execution</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">benchmarks</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">spidermonkey</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">spidermonkey</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">markdown</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">wasm</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">cycles</span>\n<span class=\"w\">      </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">115443777</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mf\">126864658.04</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">195022945</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">../</span><span class=\"n\">wasmtime</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">target</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">release</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">libwasmtime_bench_api</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">so</span>\n<span class=\"w\">      </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">122040249</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mf\">130580372.04</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">194436680</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">../</span><span class=\"n\">wasmtime</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">target</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">release</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">libwasmtime_bench_api</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">so</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Wgc</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>is the best I can get out of sightglass</p>",
        "id": 600528767,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex Crichton",
        "timestamp": 1780616503
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>so ~3% slowdown</p>",
        "id": 600529051,
        "sender_full_name": "Chris Fallin",
        "timestamp": 1780616711
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>hrm okay I can investigate</p>",
